<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1346,1445]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">
This species was collected only once in 
<collectingRegion box="[582,647,1346,1372]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">Goiás</collectingRegion>
by Glaziou (n. 
<emphasis box="[821,889,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">21154</emphasis>
) between Corumbá (currently Corumbá de 
<collectingRegion box="[1377,1444,1346,1373]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">Goiás</collectingRegion>
) and Lages in July of 1894. It was erroneously identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="O. Berg (1857" authorityName="O. Berg" authorityYear="1857" box="[803,1166,1382,1409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canescens">
<emphasis box="[803,1004,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">Myrcia canescens</emphasis>
O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Berg, O." box="[1035,1166,1382,1409]" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 656" refId="ref13590" refString="Berg, O. (1857 - 1859) Myrtaceae. In: Martius, C. F. P. von (Ed.) Flora Brasiliensis, vol. 14, pt. 1. Frid. Fleischer in Comm., Lipsiae [Leipzig] &amp; Monachii [Munich], pp. 1 - 656. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="book chapter" year="1857">Berg (1857</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
–1859: 206) but lacks the profuse white indumentum, one of the diagnostic characteristics of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[890,1093,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albotomentosa">
<emphasis box="[890,1093,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="79">M. albotomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
